To determine the difference in speed between the two cars, we calculate the speed of each car using the formula:  
\[
\text{Speed} = \frac{\text{Distance}}{\text{Time}}
\]

\[
\text{Speed of X} = \frac{320 \, \text{kms}}{8 \, \text{hrs}} = 40 \, \text{kms/hr}
\]

\]

\[
\text{Difference} = 83 \, \text{kms/hr} - 40 \, \text{kms/hr} = 43 \, \text{kms/hr}
\]

Thus, the difference in the speed of the two cars is **43 km/hr**.  

Answer: C
